Package b2bpl.graph Description

Contains classes implementing a simple control flow graph.

The AbstractFlowGraph class is a simple implementation of a control flow graph in which every node is represented by an AbstractVertex and every edge by an AbstractEdge. All the classes are abstract and can be parameterized by concrete implementations of an AbstractVertex and an AbstractEdge. Hence, in order to use the here provided implementation of a control flow graph, one should write concrete subclasses for all of the above classes parameterized with the respective concrete implementations of the AbstractVertex and AbstractEdge classes.

In addition to providing a simple flow graph datastructure, the AbstractFlowGraph class also embodies a set of algorithms related to the detection of loops and for determining some structural properties of the graph such as whether it is reducible or not.
